    "text": "By Chad Washington ,\n5 hours ago\nHOUSTON ( KIAH ) — An attorney in Houston that deals with technology companies is accused of having sex with a 16-year-old girl he met on a dating app.\nFeras Mousilli, 46, was arrested at Bush Airport on Tuesday. He has bonded out of jail and a protective order was issued, requiring him to stay away from the 16-year-old victim and her family.\nAccording to court documents, investigators found photos and video of the encounter on the teen’s phone.\nAccording to the firm’s website, Mousilli works on technology law issues and counseling tech companies.\nAccording to our news partners, court documents say that Mousilli met the victim on the dating app Bumble, and that she reported to the Texas Department of Family and Protective Services that she had intercourse with him.\nMousilli is due in court in January.\nCopyright 2024 Nexstar Media, Inc. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed. For the latest news, weather, sports, and streaming video, head to CW39 Houston.",
